the mechanisms described"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"in the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"http:\/\/www.freedesktop.org\/Standards\/basedir-spec","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"In this case the list of directories retrieved will be ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"XDG_CONFIG_DIRS"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On Windows it follows XDG Base Directory Specification if "},{"code":"XDG_CONFIG_DIRS","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is defined.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"code":"XDG_CONFIG_DIRS","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is undefined, the directory that contains application"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"data for all users is used instead. A typical path is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"C:\\Documents and Settings\\All Users\\Application Data","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This folder is used for application data","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that is not user specific. For example, an application can store"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a spell-check dictionary, a database of clip art, or a log file in the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"FOLDERID_ProgramData folder. This information will not roam and is available","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to anyone using the computer.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The return value is cached and modifying it at runtime is not supported, as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"it’s not thread-safe to modify environment variables at runtime.","type":"text"}]}]}],"references":{"http://www.freedesktop.org/Standards/basedir-spec":{"url":"http:\/\/www.freedesktop.org\/Standards\/basedir-spec","ti